- Wrong exceptions: ensure tests assert the specific Error class (TypeError vs RangeError) and exact message where tests check messages.
- ESM import errors: ensure package.json "type" is set to "module" or rename files to .mjs; adjust import paths to include .js extension when running under Node ESM.

Best practices
- Keep fizzBuzz pure and side-effect free (no console.log inside the function). Separate printing from logic.
- Use explicit validation early (fail-fast). This simplifies tests and error handling.
- Provide small helper functions only if reused (e.g., isDivisible(i, d) is overkill for this simple function).
- Provide streaming variant for huge n to avoid out-of-memory problems.

